The theorem `memLp_id_semicircleReal` states that `id ∈ Lp (semicircleReal μ v)`. The proof strategy uses `memLp_of_mem_interior_integrableExpSet`. This requires showing that the support of the distribution is contained in the set where `exp(t * x)` is bounded by `exp(|t| * (|μ| + 2 * √v))`.

